ntil a few years ago, there were two in my eyes.<br><br>1. sit down, shut up, play manasong. some bards think this is their only real use and they sit in the corner (probably afk) just playing song. fine with me since i'm a wizard, but i prefer other kinds.<br><br>2. the good bard. these know their class, can twist, know they can actually melee (gasp!), and serve as a good utility class at the same time.<br><br>3. vashon. he (and no doubt a few others) renew faith in the bard class. for anyone that has grouped with him or raided with him know what i am talking about. keeping 4 or 5 mobs mezzed while tanking, pulling, playing manasong is the norm for him.<br><br>it's also amazing how many jackass bards there are out there. vash tells me about some of them and their bragging about this or that and how they can do X etc etc.<br><br>i also feel sorry for bards since so many of their songs are in a constant state of broken. when they 'fix' one, verant is really nerfing it in a different way. poor bards<br> <p><table width="262" border="1" height="102" align="center"><tr>                               <td height="74" width="77%">                               <div align="center">                               <p><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2"><b><fontcolor="#0000CD">Crimen Talionis</font></b></font><font           face="Lucida Calligraphy,Comic Sans MS,Lucida Console,PrawnHandwrite" size="2"><br><br>                               <b><font color="#990099">FS Curmudgeon</font></b></font></p>       </div>                               </td>                                <td rowspan="2" width="23%">                               <div align="center"><a href="http://attrition.org/fs/"><imgsrc="http://www.attrition.org/fs/images/fs-sig.gif" width="100"height="100" border="0"></a></div>                               </td>                               </tr>                               <tr>                     